§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬linear functional❭ on a vector space $V$ over a field
    $𝗙$ is a linear function from $V$ to $𝗙$. ⦉

  ‖ In other words, a linear function is an element of $ℒ(V,
    𝗙)$. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We tend to denote linear functionals by $φ: V → 𝗙$, a
    mnemonic for functional. ⦉
⦉

§§ Examples ⦉
𝍫 ⦊
  ‣ ‖ Define $φ: 𝗥^3 → 𝗥$ by
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ φ(x, y, z) = 4x - 5y + 2z ⦉
      ⦉⦉

    ‖ $φ$ is a linear function on $𝗥^3$ ⦉⦉

  ‣ ‖ Define $φ: 𝗖^n → 𝗖$ by
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ φ(x_1, …, x_n) = c_1x_1 + c_2x_2 + ⋯ + c_nx_n ⦉
      ⦉
      where $c_1, …, c_n ∈ 𝗖$. ⦉

    ‖ $φ$ is a linear functional on $𝗖^n$. ⦉⦉

  ‣ Let $(c_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡} ∈ ℓ^{∞}$. Define $F_c: ℓ^1 → 𝗖$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ F_c((x_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡}) = ∑_{n = 1}^{∞} c_n x_n. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‣ ‖ As usual, denote the set of real polynomials by $𝒫(𝗥)$. ⦉

    ‖ Define $φ: 𝒫(𝗥) → 𝗥$ by
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ φ(p) = 3p''(5) + 7p(4) ⦉
      ⦉⦉

    ‖ $φ$ is a linear functional on $𝒫(𝗥)$. ⦉⦉

  ‣ ‖ As usual, denote the set of real polynomials by $𝒫(𝗥)$. ⦉

    ‖ Define $φ: 𝒫(𝗥) → 𝗥$ by
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ φ(p) = ∫_{[0,1]} p ⦉
      ⦉⦉

    ‖ $φ$ is a linear functional on $𝒫(𝗥)$. ⦉⦉
⦉

